  Source:
    Title: The Imitation of Christ
    Locus: III xli
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Sacrifice and Suffering=Contemptus Mundi
---
Unless I prepare myself with cheerful willingness to be despised and forsaken
of all creatures, and to be esteemed altogether nothing, I cannot obtain
inward peace and stability, nor be spiritually enlightened, nor be fully
united unto thee.
